block-definition.comment: Saves costume as a PNG By pumpkinhead

block.l: if (!(costume instanceof Costume)) throw new Error("Not a Costume"); var data = costume.contents.toDataURL("image/png"); var link = document.createElement("a"); link.download = costume.name + ".png"; link.href = data; link.click();

var xmlhttp = new XMLHttpRequest(); // new HttpRequest instance xmlhttp.responseType = 'json'; var theUrl = "http://192.168.137.219/jetson-interface/imagenet"; xmlhttp.open("POST", theUrl); //var canvas_pic=world.children[0].corral.stageIcon.object.fullImage().toDataURL(); var data = costume.contents.toDataURL("image/png"); xmlhttp.setRequestHeader("Content-Type", "application/json;charset=UTF-8"); xmlhttp.send(JSON.stringify({"image": data })); xmlhttp.onreadystatechange = function() { if (xmlhttp.readyState == XMLHttpRequest.DONE) { window.confidence = xmlhttp.response["confidence"]; window.className = xmlhttp.response["class"]; } }
